executor_description: Returns a list of workouts that meet the specified criteria. Query parameters can be used to filter the results.

queryParams.description: integer <int32> [ 1 .. 100 ] Default: 20 The upper limit of items to return in one request. The max is 100 and the default is 20.
integer <int32> >= 1 Default: 1 The page number of results to return
Array of strings Example: bodyPart=lower_body Any body part filters (by keys). Workouts returned will involve at least one of these body parts.
Array of strings Example: difficulty=beginner,all_levels Any difficulty filters (by keys). Workouts returned will be one of these difficulty levels.
Array of strings Example: category=strength_training,treadmill Any category filters (by keys). Workouts returned will be in at least one of these categories
Array of strings Example: equipment=dumbbells,barbell Any equipment filters (by keys). Workouts returned will feature at least one piece of this equipment.
Array of strings Example: genre=classic_rock,pop,indie Any genre filters (by keys). Workouts returned will feature music primarily in one of these genres.
integer <int32> Example: minDuration=300000 The minimum workout duration in milliseconds
integer <int32> Example: maxDuration=900000 The maximum workout duration in milliseconds.
integer <int32> Example: minIntensity=1 The minimum workout intensity on a scale of 1-5
integer <int32> Example: maxIntensity=5 The maximum workout intensity on a scale of 1-5
